{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":950,"text":"The Olympic motto is \"Citius, Altius, Fortius.\""},{"time":4081,"text":"Faster, Higher, Stronger."},{"time":6850,"text":"And athletes have fulfilled that motto rapidly."},{"time":10790,"text":"The winner of the 2012 Olympic marathon"},{"time":13946,"text":"ran two hours and eight minutes."},{"time":16262,"text":"Had he been racing against the winner"},{"time":17882,"text":"of the 1904 Olympic marathon,"},{"time":20348,"text":"he would have won by nearly an hour and a half."},{"time":23681,"text":"Now we all have this feeling"},{"time":25453,"text":"that we're somehow just getting better"},{"time":27043,"text":"as a human race, inexorably progressing,"},{"time":29383,"text":"but it's not like we've evolved into a new species"},{"time":31524,"text":"in a century."},{"time":32990,"text":"So what's going on here?"},{"time":35598,"text":"I want to take a look at what's really behind"},{"time":36959,"text":"this march of athletic progress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39649,"text":"In 1936, Jesse Owens"},{"time":41946,"text":"held the world record in the 100 meters."},{"time":44283,"text":"Had Jesse Owens been racing last year"},{"time":46990,"text":"in the world championships of the 100 meters,"},{"time":49436,"text":"when Jamaican sprinter Usain Bolt finished,"},{"time":51910,"text":"Owens would have still had 14 feet to go."},{"time":55318,"text":"That's a lot in sprinter land."},{"time":57197,"text":"To give you a sense of how much it is,"},{"time":58700,"text":"I want to share with you a demonstration"},{"time":60658,"text":"conceived by sports scientist Ross Tucker."},{"time":63670,"text":"Now picture the stadium last year"},{"time":65835,"text":"at the world championships of the 100 meters:"},{"time":68464,"text":"thousands of fans waiting with baited breath"},{"time":70563,"text":"to see Usain Bolt, the fastest man in history;"},{"time":74037,"text":"flashbulbs popping as the\nnine fastest men in the world"},{"time":76912,"text":"coil themselves into their blocks."},{"time":79475,"text":"And I want you to pretend"},{"time":80606,"text":"that Jesse Owens is in that race."},{"time":82945,"text":"Now close your eyes for a\nsecond and picture the race."},{"time":86190,"text":"Bang! The gun goes off."},{"time":87882,"text":"An American sprinter jumps out to the front."},{"time":89950,"text":"Usain Bolt starts to catch him."},{"time":91900,"text":"Usain Bolt passes him, and as\nthe runners come to the finish,"},{"time":93521,"text":"you'll hear a beep as each man crosses the line."},{"time":96198,"text":"(Beeps)"},{"time":97875,"text":"That's the entire finish of the race."},{"time":100980,"text":"You can open your eyes now."},{"time":102360,"text":"That first beep was Usain Bolt."},{"time":104970,"text":"That last beep was Jesse Owens."},{"time":107284,"text":"Listen to it again."},{"time":109461,"text":"(Beeps)"},{"time":111179,"text":"When you think of it like that,"},{"time":112279,"text":"it's not that big a difference, is it?"},{"time":114550,"text":"And then consider that Usain Bolt started"},{"time":116407,"text":"by propelling himself out of blocks"},{"time":119170,"text":"down a specially fabricated carpet"},{"time":121509,"text":"designed to allow him to travel"},{"time":123265,"text":"as fast as humanly possible."},{"time":125381,"text":"Jesse Owens, on the other hand,"},{"time":127052,"text":"ran on cinders, the ash from burnt wood,"},{"time":130643,"text":"and that soft surface stole far more energy"},{"time":132880,"text":"from his legs as he ran."},{"time":134657,"text":"Rather than blocks, Jesse\nOwens had a gardening trowel"},{"time":137620,"text":"that he had to use to dig holes\nin the cinders to start from."},{"time":141447,"text":"Biomechanical analysis of the speed"},{"time":143551,"text":"of Owens' joints shows that had been running"},{"time":146095,"text":"on the same surface as Bolt,"},{"time":147609,"text":"he wouldn't have been 14 feet behind,"},{"time":150120,"text":"he would have been within one stride."},{"time":152439,"text":"Rather than the last beep,"},{"time":154181,"text":"Owens would have been the second beep."},{"time":157121,"text":"Listen to it again."},{"time":159172,"text":"(Beeps)"},{"time":160910,"text":"That's the difference track\nsurface technology has made,"},{"time":163293,"text":"and it's done it throughout the running world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165572,"text":"Consider a longer event."},{"time":167303,"text":"In 1954, Sir Roger Bannister"},{"time":170266,"text":"became the first man to run\nunder four minutes in the mile."},{"time":173443,"text":"Nowadays, college kids do that every year."},{"time":176493,"text":"On rare occasions, a high school kid does it."},{"time":179046,"text":"As of the end of last year,"},{"time":180788,"text":"1,314 men"},{"time":183155,"text":"had run under four minutes in the mile,"},{"time":185370,"text":"but like Jesse Owens,"},{"time":186820,"text":"Sir Roger Bannister ran on soft cinders"},{"time":189562,"text":"that stole far more energy from his legs"},{"time":191386,"text":"than the synthetic tracks of today."},{"time":193749,"text":"So I consulted biomechanics experts"},{"time":195249,"text":"to find out how much slower it is to run on cinders"},{"time":197813,"text":"than synthetic tracks,"},{"time":199071,"text":"and their consensus that it's\none and a half percent slower."},{"time":202471,"text":"So if you apply a one and a half\npercent slowdown conversion"},{"time":205758,"text":"to every man who ran his sub-four mile"},{"time":207944,"text":"on a synthetic track,"},{"time":209388,"text":"this is what happens."},{"time":211084,"text":"Only 530 are left."},{"time":213413,"text":"If you look at it from that perspective,"},{"time":214810,"text":"fewer than ten new men per [year]"},{"time":217130,"text":"have joined the sub-four mile club"},{"time":218613,"text":"since Sir Roger Bannister."},{"time":220915,"text":"Now, 530 is a lot more than one,"},{"time":223982,"text":"and that's partly because\nthere are many more people"},{"time":225498,"text":"training today and they're training more intelligently."},{"time":228012,"text":"Even college kids are professional in their training"},{"time":230240,"text":"compared to Sir Roger Bannister,"},{"time":231766,"text":"who trained for 45 minutes at a time"},{"time":233225,"text":"while he ditched gynecology lectures in med school."},{"time":236315,"text":"And that guy who won the 1904 Olympic marathon"},{"time":238718,"text":"in three in a half hours,"},{"time":240429,"text":"that guy was drinking rat poison and brandy"},{"time":242566,"text":"while he ran along the course."},{"time":244598,"text":"That was his idea of a performance-enhancing drug."},{"time":247221,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":249284,"text":"Clearly, athletes have gotten more savvy"},{"time":250972,"text":"about performance-enhancing drugs as well,"},{"time":253446,"text":"and that's made a difference\nin some sports at some times,"},{"time":255717,"text":"but technology has made a difference in all sports,"},{"time":258004,"text":"from faster skis to lighter shoes."},{"time":260553,"text":"Take a look at the record for\nthe 100-meter freestyle swim."},{"time":263693,"text":"The record is always trending downward,"},{"time":266340,"text":"but it's punctuated by these steep cliffs."},{"time":269090,"text":"This first cliff, in 1956, is the introduction"},{"time":272011,"text":"of the flip turn."},{"time":273240,"text":"Rather than stopping and turning around,"},{"time":275269,"text":"athletes could somersault under the water"},{"time":277113,"text":"and get going right away in the opposite direction."},{"time":279631,"text":"This second cliff, the introduction of gutters"},{"time":282423,"text":"on the side of the pool"},{"time":283955,"text":"that allows water to splash off,"},{"time":285512,"text":"rather than becoming turbulence"},{"time":286799,"text":"that impedes the swimmers as they race."},{"time":289046,"text":"This final cliff,"},{"time":290685,"text":"the introduction of full-body"},{"time":291871,"text":"and low-friction swimsuits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293768,"text":"Throughout sports, technology has\nchanged the face of performance."},{"time":297457,"text":"In 1972, Eddy Merckx set the record"},{"time":300233,"text":"for the longest distance cycled in one hour"},{"time":302557,"text":"at 30 miles, 3,774 feet."},{"time":306605,"text":"Now that record improved and improved"},{"time":308853,"text":"as bicycles improved and became more aerodynamic"},{"time":311872,"text":"all the way until 1996,"},{"time":313486,"text":"when it was set at 35 miles, 1,531 feet,"},{"time":317921,"text":"nearly five miles farther"},{"time":320150,"text":"than Eddy Merckx cycled in 1972."},{"time":323295,"text":"But then in 2000, the International Cycling Union"},{"time":326718,"text":"decreed that anyone who wanted to hold that record"},{"time":329226,"text":"had to do so with essentially the same equipment"},{"time":332298,"text":"that Eddy Merckx used in 1972."},{"time":334963,"text":"Where does the record stand today?"},{"time":337218,"text":"30 miles, 4,657 feet,"},{"time":340840,"text":"a grand total of 883 feet"},{"time":343950,"text":"farther than Eddy Merckx cycled"},{"time":345726,"text":"more than four decades ago."},{"time":347427,"text":"Essentially the entire improvement in this record"},{"time":349808,"text":"was due to technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351860,"text":"Still, technology isn't the only\nthing pushing athletes forward."},{"time":355030,"text":"While indeed we haven't evolved"},{"time":356481,"text":"into a new species in a century,"},{"time":358198,"text":"the gene pool within competitive sports"},{"time":360158,"text":"most certainly has changed."},{"time":362550,"text":"In the early half of the 20th century,"},{"time":364459,"text":"physical education instructors and coaches"},{"time":366144,"text":"had the idea that the average body type"},{"time":368416,"text":"was the best for all athletic endeavors:"},{"time":370787,"text":"medium height, medium weight, no matter the sport."},{"time":374110,"text":"And this showed in athletes' bodies."},{"time":376082,"text":"In the 1920s, the average elite high-jumper"},{"time":378335,"text":"and average elite shot-putter\nwere the same exact size."},{"time":382050,"text":"But as that idea started to fade away,"},{"time":383960,"text":"as sports scientists and coaches realized that"},{"time":386036,"text":"rather than the average body type,"},{"time":387628,"text":"you want highly specialized bodies"},{"time":389540,"text":"that fit into certain athletic niches,"},{"time":391870,"text":"a form of artificial selection took place,"},{"time":394175,"text":"a self-sorting for bodies that fit certain sports,"},{"time":396798,"text":"and athletes' bodies became\nmore different from one another."},{"time":399458,"text":"Today, rather than the same size\nas the average elite high jumper,"},{"time":403414,"text":"the average elite shot-putter"},{"time":404428,"text":"is two and a half inches taller"},{"time":406079,"text":"and 130 pounds heavier."},{"time":409168,"text":"And this happened throughout the sports world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411087,"text":"In fact, if you plot on a height versus mass graph"},{"time":413752,"text":"one data point for each of two dozen sports"},{"time":416280,"text":"in the first half of the 20th century, it looks like this."},{"time":419565,"text":"There's some dispersal,"},{"time":421050,"text":"but it's kind of grouped\naround that average body type."},{"time":424060,"text":"Then that idea started to go away,"},{"time":425639,"text":"and at the same time, digital technology --"},{"time":427340,"text":"first radio, then television and the Internet --"},{"time":429547,"text":"gave millions, or in some cases billions, of people"},{"time":431924,"text":"a ticket to consume elite sports performance."},{"time":435103,"text":"The financial incentives and fame and glory\nafforded elite athletes skyrocketed,"},{"time":438976,"text":"and it tipped toward the tiny\nupper echelon of performance."},{"time":443169,"text":"It accelerated the artificial\nselection for specialized bodies."},{"time":446596,"text":"And if you plot a data point for these same"},{"time":448224,"text":"two dozen sports today, it looks like this."},{"time":452106,"text":"The athletes' bodies have gotten"},{"time":453533,"text":"much more different from one another."},{"time":455727,"text":"And because this chart looks like the charts"},{"time":457836,"text":"that show the expanding universe,"},{"time":459567,"text":"with the galaxies flying away from one another,"},{"time":462027,"text":"the scientists who discovered it call it"},{"time":463671,"text":"\"The Big Bang of Body Types.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":466960,"text":"In sports where height is prized, like basketball,"},{"time":469368,"text":"the tall athletes got taller."},{"time":471158,"text":"In 1983, the National Basketball Association"},{"time":474264,"text":"signed a groundbreaking agreement"},{"time":475587,"text":"making players partners in the league,"},{"time":477639,"text":"entitled to shares of ticket revenues"},{"time":479189,"text":"and television contracts."},{"time":481096,"text":"Suddenly, anybody who could be an NBA player"},{"time":483299,"text":"wanted to be,"},{"time":484495,"text":"and teams started scouring the globe"},{"time":486341,"text":"for the bodies that could\nhelp them win championships."},{"time":488621,"text":"Almost overnight,"},{"time":490364,"text":"the proportion of men in the NBA"},{"time":491742,"text":"who are at least seven feet tall doubled"},{"time":493634,"text":"to 10 percent."},{"time":495399,"text":"Today, one in 10 men in the NBA"},{"time":497422,"text":"is at least seven feet tall,"},{"time":499604,"text":"but a seven-foot-tall man is incredibly rare"},{"time":501753,"text":"in the general population --"},{"time":503272,"text":"so rare that if you know an American man"},{"time":505922,"text":"between the ages of 20 and 40"},{"time":507327,"text":"who is at least seven feet tall,"},{"time":509463,"text":"there's a 17 percent chance"},{"time":511235,"text":"he's in the NBA right now."},{"time":513040,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":515978,"text":"That is, find six honest seven footers,"},{"time":518854,"text":"one is in the NBA right now."},{"time":522084,"text":"And that's not the only way that\nNBA players' bodies are unique."},{"time":524913,"text":"This is Leonardo da Vinci's \"Vitruvian Man,\""},{"time":527528,"text":"the ideal proportions,"},{"time":528951,"text":"with arm span equal to height."},{"time":530950,"text":"My arm span is exactly equal to my height."},{"time":533458,"text":"Yours is probably very nearly so."},{"time":535594,"text":"But not the average NBA player."},{"time":537756,"text":"The average NBA player is a shade under 6'7\","},{"time":540563,"text":"with arms that are seven feet long."},{"time":542874,"text":"Not only are NBA players ridiculously tall,"},{"time":545672,"text":"they are ludicrously long."},{"time":547950,"text":"Had Leonardo wanted to draw"},{"time":548955,"text":"the Vitruvian NBA Player,"},{"time":550930,"text":"he would have needed a rectangle and an ellipse,"},{"time":552903,"text":"not a circle and a square."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555685,"text":"So in sports where large size is prized,"},{"time":557850,"text":"the large athletes have gotten larger."},{"time":559921,"text":"Conversely, in sports where\ndiminutive stature is an advantage,"},{"time":562900,"text":"the small athletes got smaller."},{"time":565117,"text":"The average elite female gymnast"},{"time":566780,"text":"shrunk from 5'3\" to 4'9\" on average"},{"time":569543,"text":"over the last 30 years,"},{"time":570880,"text":"all the better for their power-to-weight ratio"},{"time":572995,"text":"and for spinning in the air."},{"time":574765,"text":"And while the large got larger"},{"time":576127,"text":"and the small got smaller,"},{"time":577491,"text":"the weird got weirder."},{"time":579919,"text":"The average length of the forearm"},{"time":581469,"text":"of a water polo player in relation"},{"time":583220,"text":"to their total arm got longer,"},{"time":585077,"text":"all the better for a forceful throwing whip."},{"time":587206,"text":"And as the large got larger,"},{"time":588933,"text":"small got smaller, and the weird weirder."},{"time":591303,"text":"In swimming, the ideal body type"},{"time":593496,"text":"is a long torso and short legs."},{"time":595391,"text":"It's like the long hull of a canoe"},{"time":597330,"text":"for speed over the water."},{"time":599036,"text":"And the opposite is advantageous in running."},{"time":600801,"text":"You want long legs and a short torso."},{"time":602816,"text":"And this shows in athletes' bodies today."},{"time":605012,"text":"Here you see Michael Phelps,"},{"time":606607,"text":"the greatest swimmer in history,"},{"time":608071,"text":"standing next to Hicham El Guerrouj,"},{"time":610940,"text":"the world record holder in the mile."},{"time":612927,"text":"These men are seven inches different in height,"},{"time":615744,"text":"but because of the body types"},{"time":616946,"text":"advantaged in their sports,"},{"time":618809,"text":"they wear the same length pants."},{"time":621197,"text":"Seven inches difference in height,"},{"time":622691,"text":"these men have the same length legs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625211,"text":"Now in some cases, the search for bodies"},{"time":627169,"text":"that could push athletic performance forward"},{"time":629142,"text":"ended up introducing into the competitive world"},{"time":631785,"text":"populations of people that weren't\npreviously competing at all,"},{"time":634924,"text":"like Kenyan distance runners."},{"time":637676,"text":"We think of Kenyans as being great marathoners."},{"time":641006,"text":"Kenyans think of the Kalenjin tribe"},{"time":643384,"text":"as being great marathoners."},{"time":645484,"text":"The Kalenjin make up just 12 percent"},{"time":647579,"text":"of the Kenyan population"},{"time":649376,"text":"but the vast majority of elite runners."},{"time":651545,"text":"And they happen, on average,"},{"time":652851,"text":"to have a certain unique physiology:"},{"time":654955,"text":"legs that are very long"},{"time":656036,"text":"and very thin at their extremity,"},{"time":658574,"text":"and this is because they have their ancestry"},{"time":659992,"text":"at very low latitude"},{"time":661427,"text":"in a very hot and dry climate,"},{"time":663842,"text":"and an evolutionary adaptation to that"},{"time":665732,"text":"is limbs that are very long"},{"time":666690,"text":"and very thin at the extremity"},{"time":668209,"text":"for cooling purposes."},{"time":669983,"text":"It's the same reason that a radiator has long coils,"},{"time":673012,"text":"to increase surface area compared to volume"},{"time":674854,"text":"to let heat out,"},{"time":676796,"text":"and because the leg is like a pendulum,"},{"time":678309,"text":"the longer and thinner it is at the extremity,"},{"time":679966,"text":"the more energy-efficient it is to swing."},{"time":682745,"text":"To put Kalenjin running success in perspective,"},{"time":685339,"text":"consider that 17 American men in history"},{"time":688066,"text":"have run faster than two hours and 10 minutes"},{"time":690695,"text":"in the marathon."},{"time":691984,"text":"That's a four-minute-and-58-second-per-mile pace."},{"time":695031,"text":"Thirty-two Kalenjin men did that last October."},{"time":697966,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":700060,"text":"That's from a source population the size"},{"time":701881,"text":"of metropolitan Atlanta."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704708,"text":"Still, even changing technology"},{"time":706282,"text":"and the changing gene pool in sports"},{"time":707888,"text":"don't account for all of the changes in performance."},{"time":710361,"text":"Athletes have a different mindset than they once did."},{"time":713251,"text":"Have you ever seen in a movie when someone gets"},{"time":714620,"text":"an electrical shock"},{"time":715892,"text":"and they're thrown across a room?"},{"time":718215,"text":"There's no explosion there."},{"time":719786,"text":"What's happening when that happens is that"},{"time":721024,"text":"the electrical impulse is causing"},{"time":722486,"text":"all their muscle fibers to twitch at once,"},{"time":724616,"text":"and they're throwing themselves across the room."},{"time":727210,"text":"They're essentially jumping."},{"time":729107,"text":"That's the power"},{"time":730284,"text":"that's contained in the human body."},{"time":732233,"text":"But normally we can't access nearly all of it."},{"time":734460,"text":"Our brain acts as a limiter,"},{"time":736479,"text":"preventing us from accessing\nall of our physical resources,"},{"time":738774,"text":"because we might hurt ourselves,"},{"time":740015,"text":"tearing tendons or ligaments."},{"time":741707,"text":"But the more we learn about\nhow that limiter functions,"},{"time":744730,"text":"the more we learn how we can push it back"},{"time":746610,"text":"just a bit,"},{"time":748050,"text":"in some cases by convincing the brain"},{"time":750482,"text":"that the body won't be in mortal danger"},{"time":752256,"text":"by pushing harder."},{"time":754066,"text":"Endurance and ultra-endurance sports"},{"time":755685,"text":"serve as a great example."},{"time":757257,"text":"Ultra-endurance was once thought to be harmful"},{"time":759379,"text":"to human health,"},{"time":760794,"text":"but now we realize"},{"time":762212,"text":"that we have all these traits"},{"time":763308,"text":"that are perfect for ultra-endurance:"},{"time":766412,"text":"no body fur and a glut of sweat glands"},{"time":769336,"text":"that keep us cool while running;"},{"time":770952,"text":"narrow waists and long legs compared to our frames;"},{"time":774352,"text":"large surface area of joints for shock absorption."},{"time":777270,"text":"We have an arch in our foot that acts like a spring,"},{"time":780004,"text":"short toes that are better for pushing off"},{"time":782107,"text":"than for grasping tree limbs,"},{"time":783781,"text":"and when we run,"},{"time":784908,"text":"we can turn our torso and our shoulders"},{"time":786433,"text":"like this while keeping our heads straight."},{"time":788477,"text":"Our primate cousins can't do that."},{"time":789960,"text":"They have to run like this."},{"time":792270,"text":"And we have big old butt muscles"},{"time":794336,"text":"that keep us upright while running."},{"time":796423,"text":"Have you ever looked at an ape's butt?"},{"time":798141,"text":"They have no buns because they don't run upright."},{"time":801146,"text":"And as athletes have realized"},{"time":802533,"text":"that we're perfectly suited for ultra-endurance,"},{"time":805090,"text":"they've taken on feats"},{"time":806137,"text":"that would have been unthinkable before,"},{"time":808546,"text":"athletes like Spanish endurance racer Kílian Jornet."},{"time":812449,"text":"Here's Kílian running up the Matterhorn."},{"time":814449,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":815961,"text":"With a sweatshirt there tied around his waist."},{"time":818570,"text":"It's so steep he can't even run here."},{"time":820292,"text":"He's pulling up on a rope."},{"time":821945,"text":"This is a vertical ascent"},{"time":823282,"text":"of more than 8,000 feet,"},{"time":825391,"text":"and Kílian went up and down"},{"time":827058,"text":"in under three hours."},{"time":829439,"text":"Amazing."},{"time":831358,"text":"And talented though he is,"},{"time":832547,"text":"Kílian is not a physiological freak."},{"time":835371,"text":"Now that he has done this,"},{"time":837050,"text":"other athletes will follow,"},{"time":838961,"text":"just as other athletes followed"},{"time":840478,"text":"after Sir Roger Bannister"},{"time":842052,"text":"ran under four minutes in the mile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844190,"text":"Changing technology, changing genes,"},{"time":845817,"text":"and a changing mindset."},{"time":848215,"text":"Innovation in sports,"},{"time":849999,"text":"whether that's new track surfaces"},{"time":851656,"text":"or new swimming techniques,"},{"time":853120,"text":"the democratization of sport,"},{"time":854990,"text":"the spread to new bodies"},{"time":856331,"text":"and to new populations around the world,"},{"time":858916,"text":"and imagination in sport,"},{"time":860969,"text":"an understanding of what the human body"},{"time":862405,"text":"is truly capable of,"},{"time":864186,"text":"have conspired to make athletes stronger,"},{"time":866078,"text":"faster, bolder,"},{"time":868601,"text":"and better than ever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870578,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872934,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}